    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-29T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-29T09:00:00-05:00" n="274"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114 EW/12–2944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HWA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-29T17:00:00+03:00"
                            >December 29, 1944—5 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 30—4:30 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5053. I have received a letter from Vyshinski (<gloss target="#t_ReEmbs1"
                        >ReEmbs</gloss> 4645 December 5, 1 p. m.)<note n="1" xml:id="d274fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> stating that Lieutenant General <persName>K. D.
                        Golubev</persName> and Major General <persName corresp="#p_S9">N. V.
                        Slavin</persName> have been appointed by the Soviet Government to conduct
                    negotiations with General <persName corresp="#p_D1">Deane</persName> on
                    questions connected with the plan mutually to repatriate American and Soviet
                    prisoners of war and civilians in accordance with the principles set forth in
                        <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName>’s letter to <persName
                        corresp="#p_KGF1">Kennan</persName> of November 25. The pertinent sections
                    of <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName>’s letter were repeated to the
                    Department in Embassy’s telegram 4526 of November 27.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d274fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
